---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import profilepic from "../assets/rayosciencefestival.webp";
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Home"
	desc="Rayo is a PhD candidate at the Centre for Doctoral Training in Designing Responsible Natural Language Processing at the University of Edinburgh."
	image=""
	imageAlt=""
	>
	<div class="max-w-7xl mt-8 md:mt-24 mx-auto flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-center gap-x-12 xl:gap-x-24 gap-y-8">
			<header class="flex-col mx-auto md:mx-0 md:pl-6 items-center text-center">
				<div class="relative w-[250px] h-[322px] bg-black rounded-t-[100px] rounded-b-lg border-2 overflow-hidden">
					<Image
						width={500}
						class="absolute top-0 left-0 hover:opacity-15 transition"
						src={profilepic}
						alt="Rayo sitting on a sailing boat smiling at the camera"
					/>
					<p class="text-white pt-[190px]">
						Photo by Chris Scott
					</p>
				</div>
			</header>
			<main class="max-w-[64ch] mx-auto md:mx-0 px-6 md:pr-6">
				<div class="text-center md:text-left">
					<p class="mb-0 -ml-7.5 text-lg">
						👋 Hoi! I'm
					</p>
					<h1 class="font-semibold text-5xl leading-12 tracking-widest mb-4">
						<span class="swsh">R</span>AYO
						<br />
						<span class="pl-0">VERWE&IJlig;</span>
					</h1>
					<small class="block text-base mb-8">
						<span class="hidden md:inline-block">&rarr;&nbsp;</span>
						<em>That's /rah-yo ver-wai/ and I use he/they pronouns</em>
					</small>
				</div>
				
				<p>Currently...</p>
				<ul>
					<li class="list-['🏫']">
						A <strong>PhD candidate</strong> at the Centre for Doctoral Training in <a href="https://responsiblenlp.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Designing Responsible Natural Language Processing</a> at the University of Edinburgh
						<ul class="mt-4">
							<li class="list-['🏗️']">
								My work investigates the <strong>inclusion of children as fully-fledged research partners in the creation of NLP-based tools for education</strong>, employing the product design process as a participatory, constructionist curriculum to enable profound learning about emerging technologies such as generative AI
							</li>
							<li class="list-['🧑‍🏫']">
								I am supervised by <a href="https://homepages.inf.ed.ac.uk/fmcneill/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Prof Fiona McNeill</a>, <a href="https://www.de.ed.ac.uk/people/dr-cara-wilson" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Dr Cara Wilson</a>, and <a href="https://www.de.ed.ac.uk/people/valentina-andries" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Dr Valentina Andries</a>, and am affiliated with <a href="https://designinformatics.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Design Informatics</a> and the <a href="https://technomoralfutures.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Centre for Technomoral Futures</a>
							</li>
						</ul>
					</li>
					<li class="list-['💾']">A trustee of <a href="https://prewired.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Prewired</a>, an Edinburgh charity that runs a weekly after-school coding club for young people</li>
				</ul>
				
				<h2>
					Verwe&IJlig;zingen
				</h2>
				<p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
					<strong>ver&middot;'wij&middot;zing</strong> <em>(de, v., mv: -en)</em> "reference".
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li class="list-['🩺']">
						From 2021&ndash;2025, I was the chief technology officer of <a href="https://voxsio.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Voxsio</a>, building ethical and engaging digital health apps in partnership with the NHS
					</li>
					<li class="list-['🎨']">
						In early 2025, as part of my research, I ran a workshop at 7 Scottish and Dutch primary schools, asking students to design what they imagined AI at school would look like in the future. <a href="/designing-future-ai-schools">All their designs are showcased here!</a>
					</li>
					<li class="list-['🤖']">
						At the 2023 Scottish AI Summit in Glasgow I hosted a workshop called &ldquo;Building Inclusive AI: Language, Dialect, and Diversity&rdquo; that <a href="https://www.scottishaisummit.com/workshop-building-inclusive-ai-language-dialect-and-diversity" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">you can watch some bits of</a> if you're interested
					</li>
					<li class="list-['🎓']">
						My 2021 MSc dissertation, &ldquo;An Online Research Environment for Behavioural Studies into Reinforcement Learning&rdquo;, can be <a href="/docs/Verweij2021-OnlineResearchEnvironment.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">read here</a>
					</li>
					<li class="list-['🌮']">
						In 2020 I built <a href="https://rayoverweij.github.io/tacotab/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">TacoTab</a>, a web app for tabulating World Schools-style debating tournaments, for the <a href="https://debate.bard.edu" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Bard Debate Union</a>&mdash;it still holds up quite well!
					</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>Contact</h2>
				<p>📧 rayo [dot] verweij [at] ed [dot] ac [dot] uk or 🦋 <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/rayo.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Bluesky</a> or 👔 <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/rayo-verweij" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a></p>

				<footer class="mt-40 mb-20 text-gray-500">
					&copy; Rayo Verweij <span id="date"></span>.
				</footer>
			</main>
		</div>

		<script>
			const year = new Date().getFullYear();
			document.getElementById("date")!.innerText = year.toString();
		</script>
</BaseLayout>
